locations.title: Raider-Occupied Buildings
locations.description:
East of the [Super Duper Mart](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71813), raiders have taken over three buildings and built walkways between them.

Search the buildings to find an ammo box, jet, chem box, cooking station, and safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.description:
Can be accessed through the adjacent subway station or through a staff door located on the eastern side of the building.

Both entrances require either the door lock to be picked or the player to pass an easy speech check on the adjacent intercom beside the doors.

locations.title: Union's Hope Cathedral
locations.description: An unmarked location you can enter. Inside, you'll find a sleeping bag, ammo box, caps stash, suitcase, some glowing fungus / brain fungus growths, and a first aid kit.

locations.title: Holy Mission Congregation
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through the church's front or side doors. Inside, you'll find a few ghouls and junk items - plus a 10mm pistol in the preacher's podium.

locations.title: Graveyard
locations.description: An unmarked location visited during [The Gilded Grasshopper](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442649) quest. Occupied by Ghouls.

locations.title: Makeshift Tunnel Camp
locations.description: A small tunnel with a mattress in it can be found west of [Sunshine Tidings Co-op](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72029). Search it to find a few radroaches, a suitcase, and a brain fungus growth.

locations.title: Fraternal Post 115
locations.description: Occupied by Super Mutants.

locations.title: Lexington Parking Garage
locations.description:
An unmarked location. The area connected to the open world has some ammunition and miscellaneous loot containers, with the door to an enclosed interior found near a ramp up onto the roof.

Inside, you'll find several ghouls and a friendly Protectron that can be activated after hacking a novice-level terminal. Loot includes a few first aid kits, glowing fungus growths, corpses, and an ammo box.

locations.title: Laundromat
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a white door beneath the laundromat sign. Loot includes a first aid kit, junk items, and an overdue book.

locations.title: Lexington Pharmacy
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a white door beneath a 'drugs' sign. Inside, you'll find a first aid kit, [Stimpak](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441505), junk, jet, and Rad-X.

locations.title: Underwater Chest
locations.description: A boat carrying a steamer trunk sunk to the bottom of the lake here. The trunk has a novice-difficulty lock.

locations.title: The Switchboard
locations.description: Under the railroad, in a drainage pipe covered by foliage. You'll need to hack a Master-level terminal to gain access.

locations.title: Abandoned House
locations.description: Unmarked location directly southeast of *Bunker Hill* with the three Control Subject's Recordings and a Glowing One fight.

locations.title: Root Cellar
locations.description: Found behind the northernmost house in Sanctuary. Contains three gold bars, plenty of food, and a safe with an advanced lock.

locations.title: Compound
locations.description: The sewer is a small subterranean section accessible through a door inside a big pipe. The pipe is based partially underwater in Mystic Lake, to the west of Covenant. Visited during the quest "Human Error"

locations.title: Greenbriar Radio Signal Source
locations.description:
A distress signal originating from an underground bunker. You'll find the hatch here, hidden beneath some bushes near a barrel and crate at the edge of a clearing with a cooking station. Once inside the bunker, interact with the ham radio to turn off the distress signal.

Extend the satellites at [Radio Tower 3SM-U81](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71990) to pick up the signal.

**Warning:** High-Level Mirelurk Queen will spawn in the river.

locations.title: University Point Pharmacy
locations.description: If the Vault-Tec Workshop DLC is installed, it acts as one of the exits from Vault 88.

locations.title: Default Radio Signal Source
locations.description:
A radio signal originating from the basement of a ruined house. Extend the satellites at [Relay Tower OMC-810](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71992) to pick up the signal.

To enter the basement, use the cellar door on the side of the house. Interact with the basement ham radio to turn off the radio signal.

locations.title: Nautical Radio Signal Source
locations.description:
A mayday signal originating from the Western Bell vessel. Enter the fishing boat cabin and interact with the ham radio to turn off the mayday signal.

Extend the satellites at [Radio Tower 3SM-U81](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71990) to pick up the signal.

locations.title: Trader's Shack
locations.description:
**Location:** West of [Ranger Cabin](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71874)

**Note:** Trade here or steal a small garden of wild corn and tato fruit.

locations.title: Raider Shack
locations.description: Shack with Raider, Attack Dog, and corpse.

locations.title: Shenley's Oyster Bar
locations.description: Unmarked location, west of [Hubris Comics](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71840). Neon sign outside.

locations.title: Abandoned Store
locations.description:
- Day Tripper x2
- Short Syringer Rifle
- Vegetables
- Nuka-Cola

locations.title: Mole Rat Den
locations.description:
Directly south of the station is the entrance to the Mole Rat Den unmarked location.

Notable loot:
- [Fusion Core](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71466)
- [Trashbusters Award](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440506)
- Safe (Novice lock)

locations.title: 35 Court
locations.description: Unmarked location with a Sentry Bot, an Assaultron and X-01 Power Armor

locations.title: Commonwealth Bank
locations.description:
An unmarked location found south of [Faneuil Hall](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71848). Inside you'll find a safe with a novice-difficulty lock, a police protectron that can be activated with a novice-level terminal, miscellaneous loot containers, and a few glowing fungus growths.

The vault (accessed via an expert-level terminal) has two more safes of expert and advanced level difficulty, a duffle bag, and some more junk.

locations.title: Concord Civic Access (East)
locations.description: A cellar door found behind the bus stop leads to an underground sewage maintenance path that runs under Concord. Connects to [Concord Civic Access (Central)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=401374) and [Concord Civic Access (West)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441297).

locations.title: Concord Civic Access (Central)
locations.description:
Underground sewage maintenance path that runs under Concord. Connects to [Concord Civic Access (East)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=401373). 

Access is revealed after the Deathclaw pops out of the ground during [When Freedom Calls](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350644).

locations.title: Drug Den
locations.description:
Unmarked location filled with raiders. Accessed through a red door across the street from a "BBQ BUFFET" sign.

Expect to find a bed, plenty of chems, and a steamer trunk.

locations.title: Mean Pastries
locations.description: Unmarked location, entered through a green door beneath a 'Joe's Spuckies' sign. Inside you'll find junk, food, and a safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Observation Post
locations.description: A small observation post, marked with one of the railroad's 'ally' murals, is on a hill overlooking [Vault 111](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72064). You can find a few cartons of water here.

locations.title: Tiny Shed
locations.description: Pick through the novice-difficulty lock for some unremarkable loot.

locations.title: Makeshift Tent
locations.description: A small tent with a first aid kit can be found here. There may also be a settler nearby asking for water.

locations.title: Raider Camp
locations.description: A small group of raiders (and their dog) have set up a camp under this radio tower.

locations.title: Military Vehicle
locations.description: A military vehicle is surrounded by radioactive barrels here. You can find a first aid kit inside, and an ammo box near the barrels.

locations.title: Campsite
locations.description: Near a collapsed house. Loot includes a cooler, duffel bag, two bottles of wine and a bottle of Nuka-Cola that can be Quantum depending on your level when you visit.

locations.title: Wrecked House
locations.description: Overlooking the lake. Expect to find some food, a Nuka-Cola, a mattress, and a safe with an advanced lock. Plus a couple of creepy mannequins.

locations.title: Abandoned Trailer
locations.description: A stone's throw from [Abernathy Farm](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72033). Expect to find a mattress, ammo box, bobby pin box, toolbox, cooler, and first aid kit.

locations.title: Concord Water Tower
locations.description: On a hill overlooking the area. Expect to find some purified water and a first aid kit at its base, and a half-buried steamer trunk by walking away from the door in a straight line.

locations.title: Makeshift Shooting Range
locations.description: A lone scavenger can be found shooting at bottles on top of posts here.

locations.title: Raider Camp
locations.description: A few raiders have set up camp with their dog beneath a gnarled tree here. Expect to find a cooler, some sleeping bags, and a cap stash in an open safe at the base of a brick monument nearby.

locations.title: Water Filtration Stash
locations.description:
At the top of a hill overlooking the lake. Expect to find a suitcase, snubnosed .44 pistol and bobby pin box near a skeleton, plus some RadAway and Rad-X in a box within the grey cylinder.

If you're *still* not satisfied, follow a pipe down to the water's edge and flip a switch to open the yellow machine's lid. This will reveal three caps stashes.

locations.title: Raider Den
locations.description: A raider and dog have settled into this tiny den built between some rocks at the top of the hill. Expect to find an ammo box, mattress, and chem cooler.

locations.title: Scavenger Shack
locations.description: A scavenger lives in a tiny shack here, and will turn hostile if you get too close. Expect to find a sleeping bag, wooden crate, and few bottles of alcohol.

locations.title: Crashed Vertibird
locations.description: A pre-war Vertibird crashed here and has decayed considerably. Not much in the way of loot, but you can find a brown flight helmet in the pilot's seat and some [Power Armor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71731) nearby.

locations.title: Dismembered Traders
locations.description:
A pair of traders met a terrible fate, and you can find their remains in the bathtub and barrel here. Also expect to find a cooler and crate with a novice-difficulty lock.

*Note - if you nudge the body in the barrel, physics glitches can make it start spinning wildly!*

locations.title: Shack Beneath the Flyover
locations.description: A reasonably-sized shack can be found directly below the flyover. Expect to find a bed, ammo box, food, and other miscellaneous loot.

locations.title: Sunken Containers
locations.description:
Swim to the bottom of the lake to find a steamer trunk and explosives box among the barrels.

*Power armor recommended - the bottom of the lake is extremely radioactive.*

locations.title: Railroad Cache
locations.description: Inside a truck's storage trailer found at the edge of the lake. Expect to find an explosives box and bottlecap mine, even if you've had no prior involvement with the Railroad.

locations.title: Truck and Trailer
locations.description: A wrecked truck can be found at the edge of the map. Expect to find a steamer trunk in its trailer, and not much else.

locations.title: Hideout
locations.description:
An unmarked location found underneath the bridge. You can find a few sleeping bags and several hostile ghouls inside.

**Notable Loot:**
- [Fusion Core](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=356187)

locations.title: Sunken Container
locations.description:
A steamer trunk can be found at the bottom of the sea, beneath a stone arch.

Finding it will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - Difficult to Kill](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440538)

*Note - the nearby bathtub has a few references to Die Hard - namely some duct tape, a lighter, and a teddy bear!*

locations.title: Crashed Plane
locations.description: A plane has crashed into the rocks on a small island here. You can find a red flight helmet under the wing and a metal box (alongside some harvestable plants) under the cockpit.

locations.title: Sunken Containers
locations.description:
A steamer trunk can be found at the bottom of the sea, in an upside-down boat. You can also find a first aid kit next to the doorway.

Looting the trunk will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - Trapped for Days](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440545)

locations.title: Floating Platform
locations.description: A wooden platform is floating on the surface between two rocks here. Loot includes a wooden box, bobby pins, and some junk.

locations.title: Floating Outpost
locations.description: A floating structure can be found near the rocks here. Loot includes duffel bags and junk, with a metal box on top of the half-submerged boat nearby.

locations.title: Floating Outpost
locations.description: A large wooden platform is floating freely in the sea here. Expect to find a few mattresses, junk items, a crate, and a Mutfruit plant.

locations.title: Sunken Cargo Ship
locations.description: An enormous cargo ship can be found at the bottom of the sea here. No loot to speak of.

locations.title: Sunken Containers
locations.description:
A rowboat can be found at the bottom of the sea, with a steamer trunk and a tool case on it.

Looting the trunk will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - X Marks the Spot](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440616)

You're all but guaranteed to start drowning on the way down to it or back up, so bring plenty of Stimpaks, a suit of Power Armor, or the Aqua Boy / Aqua Girl perk to boost your air supply.

locations.title: Backyard Bunker
locations.description:
Unmarked location. Entered through cellar doors in the shed next to a yellow house where you find [Hammer's Holotape](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=116914).

**Notable loot:**
- [David's Holotape](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=119694)
- [Nuka-Cola Quantum](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440650)
- Hazmat Suit
- Safe with an expert-difficulty lock

locations.title: Malden Drainage
locations.description:
An unmarked location north of [Taffington Boathouse](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72043), entered by venturing into the dark drainpipe.

**Notable Loot:**
- [Pledge Initiation Instructions](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=440655)
- [Fusion Core](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71523)

locations.title: Raider Camp
locations.description:
A raider has set up an unusually-decorated camp around the truck here. Watch out for turrets near the front, and a pair of attack dogs.

Expect to find a sleeping bag, ammo box, explosives box with a novice-difficulty lock, and cooking station.

locations.title: Hilltop Shack
locations.description: A shack can be found on top of the hill here. Expect to find a bed, cooler, some junk, a weapons workbench and a terminal with an expert-difficulty lock. Hacking into it will let you unleash a Police protectron found underneath the shack.

locations.title: Wrecked Bus
locations.description: A yellow bus can be found by the side of the road here, surrounded by Stingwings. Expect to find two suitcases and a lunch pail near the driver's seat.

locations.title: The Behemoth's Favourite Monkey
locations.description:
Jangles the Moon Monkey can be found in a small red car here. Picking it up spawns a Super Mutant Behemoth.

Search the surrounding area to find a the corpses of a raider, settler, and glowing one alongside a chem box and caps stash.

locations.title: Charlestown Laundry
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a white door near a red truck.

**Notable Loot:**
- [La Coiffe](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71464)
- [Nuka-Cola Quantum](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71674) on a desk behind the door with a novice-difficulty lock.
- Safe with an Expert-difficulty lock (in the same room as the Nuka-Cola Quantum)

locations.title: Construction Site Warehouse
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a door near a Super Mutant barricade and hanging meat bag.

locations.title: Cambridge Church
locations.description: An unmarked and unremarkable location near the flyover. Infested by feral ghouls, and visited during [Boston After Dark](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=354348).

locations.title: Mass Chemical
locations.description: An unmarked location. Inside, you'll find a chemistry station, weapons workbench, and novice-difficulty terminal that can activate a construction protectron.

locations.title: Cambridge Construction Site
locations.description: Unmarked location. Filled with super mutants.

locations.title: Science Center Gift Shop
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a blue door near the bridge. Inside, you'll find a chemistry station, several junk items, a safe with a novice-difficulty lock, and a [Mr. Handy](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441176) that acts as a trader.

locations.title: Lonely Ghoul
locations.description: A small raft in the middle of the river is home to a Glowing One that's all but defenceless. On the underside of the raft, you'll find that it was being kept afloat by a few radioactive barrels - which explains a lot!

locations.title: Wrecked Apartment
locations.description: Climb a pile of rubble to find some junk and a safe with a master-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Apartments
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a blue door beneath the cigarette advertisement. 

Inside, you'll find raiders and junk items on your way up the stairs, with the best loot (food, chems, an overdue book and a bottlecap mine) on the top floor. You can also sleep here thanks to a bed and sleeping bag on the top floor.

locations.title: Abandoned Boat
locations.description: Swim up to this wooden boat to find an unlocked safe.

locations.title: Marlborough House
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a white door behind some sandbags. Inside, you'll find a [Stimpak](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441184), the [Esplanade Mission Brief](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441183) note, several sleeping bags, junk items, and varied loot containers.

locations.title: Bridgeway Trust
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through the white double doors beneath a large 'BANK' sign. Inside, you'll mostly find junk items (plus a pair of 10mm pistols from would-be bank robbers), with the real good stuff found when you hack into a master-difficulty terminal and unlock the vault door.

The vault is home to four gold bars and sixteen safes, fifteen of which are locked with difficulties ranging from Novice to Master.

locations.title: Abandoned Boat
locations.description: Swim up to this wooden boat to find an unlocked safe inside.

locations.title: Utility Tunnel
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a door at the bottom of some stairs inside the [Boston Police Rationing Site](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71936).

Connects to a large network of tunnels that can be accessed through [Mass Pike Tunnel West](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71955) and [Mass Pike Tunnel East](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71956).

locations.title: Caged Dog
locations.description: A dog named Teddy is trapped in a cage here. Pick through the door's advanced-level lock to return him to his owner, [Eleanor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441193).

locations.title: Sunken Boat
locations.description: A boat can be found in the river here, with parts of it sticking out of the water. Swim inside to find a footlocker with a USCG Lockup Password inside.

locations.title: Sunken Container
locations.description: An industrial trunk can be found at the bottom of [Lake Cochituate](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71984) here, near a log and some radioactive barrels.

locations.title: Lakeside Shacks
locations.description:
A reasonably sized settler camp has been invaded by mirelurks here. Expect to find a cooking station, some junk, a bed, plenty of corpses, and robot model kit parts in a secondary shack out the back.

One of three places where robot model kit parts can be found. The other two are found at the [Poseidon Reservoir](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71888) and [Mahkra Fishpacking](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71884).

locations.title: Substation
locations.description: At the edge of the map, you can find a Super Mutant Behemoth fighting a Deathclaw or two among the power infrastructure. Loot is sparse, but you can find some glowing fungus growths inside the warehouse nearby.

locations.title: Civil Alert System Broadcast Signal Source
locations.description: A hatch at the base of the west satellite dish leads to the Military Bunker, an unmarked location. Once inside, you can interact with the ham radio to turn off the broadcast started when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0BB-915](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71993)

locations.title: Distress Signal Source
locations.description:
A hatch can be at the base of two trees outside the large orange-and-white trailer northwest of the pool in [Fiddler's Green Trailer Estates](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71860). Once inside, you can interact with a ham radio to turn off the distress signal started when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0BB-915](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71993).

The bunker is also home to a bed, several food items, and a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Raider Radio Signal Source
locations.description:
A hatch outside the lone raider's shack leads down to an unmarked bunker. Once inside, you can interact with the ham radio to turn off the signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0BB-915](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71993).

The bunker is also home to a baseball bat, jet, psychotats, a chem cooler with a novice-difficulty lock, and a single 10mm round.

locations.title: Military Vehicle
locations.description: A military vehicle can be found here, totally surrounded by land mines. Expect to find a duffle bag, some food, a silver locket, a dirty army helmet, and a rifle.

locations.title: Canister Launching Shack
locations.description:
A shack overlooking the area has some explosive canisters you can attack to launch them into the air. Hold down the 'pick up' button to move other canisters into position and continue the fun.

You can also find a bed and cooking stove here.

locations.title: Makeshift Camp
locations.description: A mattress, cooking station, suitcase and caps stash can be found at the edge of the water here. Don't get too comfortable - the area is home to several mirelurks.

locations.title: Gunner Camp
locations.description:
Here, you'll find an elevator guarded by a Gunner and a turret. Press the button, and you'll be taken up to a flyover where a few more Gunners can be found alongside a cooking station, weapons workbench, a couple of beds, and some loot containers.

The view's pretty good up there, too!

locations.title: Safe on the Flyover
locations.description: At the end of a flyover (accessed by using an elevator beneath the [Gunner Camp](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441249)). You'll find some pre-war money, a snubnosed .44 pistol, a duffle bag, and a safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Bethany's Shack
locations.description: A shack owned by [Bethany](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441255). Expect to find a weapons workbench, cooking station, overdue book, mattress, and plenty of rads - it's built on top of a toxic pond!

locations.title: Carhenge
locations.description: Several cars have been stuck together in strange shapes somewhat resembling Stonehenge here. A Super Mutant Behemoth can be found in the area after reaching level 12.

locations.title: Raider Shack
locations.description: Two raiders live in a shack by the roadside. Inside, you'll find a bed, chemistry workstation, and wooden crate.

locations.title: Concrete Building
locations.description: A small concrete building can be found here. Inside, you'll need to hack into a novice-difficulty terminal to access the main attractions- a bed, explosives box, and destroyed Mr. Gutsy.

locations.title: Billboard Camp
locations.description: Behind the billboard, you can walk up a fallen tree to find a mattress, chem cooler, first aid kit, and ammo box.

locations.title: Concord Speakeasy
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a shop with a white door in the middle of the street opposite the [Museum of Freedom](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71849). Can also be entered through the back door in the next street over.

**Notable loot:**

- Safe with an advanced-difficulty lock behind the bar on the ground floor
- Steamer trunk and 10mm pistol in the room behind a door with an advanced-difficulty lock on the upper floor
- 2x X-Cell near a bed on the upper floor
- 2x Day Tripper and 2 machetes in an en-suite bathroom on the upper floor

locations.title: Workhouse
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a white door near a lantern.

**Notable Loot:**
- Cooler and duffle bag near a dress-wearing skeleton on the second-to-top floor
- Safe with an advanced-difficulty lock on the top floor

locations.title: Lootable House
locations.description: One of a handful of non-boarded-up houses in the area. You can find a first aid kit, caps stash, a few food items, and a safe with a novice-difficulty lock under the bed.

locations.title: Seat with a View
locations.description: On some high-up rocks, you can find a chair facing the [Red Rocket Truck Stop](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72034) - the perfect place to admire your settlement. An ammo box and toolbox can be found nearby.

locations.title: Lootable House
locations.description: One of a handful of non-boarded-up houses in the area. You can find a mattress, chem box, caps stash, [Nuka-Cola Quantum](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=123325), some food, a bobby pin box, and a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock inside.

locations.title: Concord Civic Access (West)
locations.description: Cellar door found between two buildings, leading to an underground sewage maintenance path that runs under Concord. Connects to [Concord Civic Access (Central)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=401374) and [Concord Civic Access (East)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=401373).

locations.title: Concord Church
locations.description: Next to the [Museum of Freedom](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71849). On the upper floor you'll find a safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Lootable House
locations.description: One of a handful of non-boarded-up houses in the area. Inside, you'll find a chem box, caps stash, bobby pin box, some food, a sleeping bag, and a safe with a novice-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Gunner Camp
locations.description: Here, you'll find an elevator that can take you up to the top of the flyover. On it, you'll find a small Gunner camp that's home to an Assaultron and some loot containers.

locations.title: Tiny Diner
locations.description: An unmarked building with a great view of the water. Loot includes a cola machine that can contain Nuka-Cherry or Quantum depending on your level, beer, and a safe with an expert-difficulty lock behind the counter.

locations.title: Red Rocket
locations.description: Home to a few junk items and a power armor station. Climb a nearby truck to get onto the roof, where you'll find an armor workbench, weapons workbench, and sniper rifle.

locations.title: Sunken Boat
locations.description: At the end of a pier, you can swim down to find a sunken boat. Check the inside to find a stimpak and wooden crate with an advanced-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Garage
locations.description:
A reasonably sized building marked with one of the railroad's 'cache' murals. Walk up a tree leaning against the back wall to find a caps stash and supply box, then drop through a hole in the ceiling to find a power armor station, first aid kit, and explosives box with a novice-difficulty lock.

You can also find a protectron model kit next to the power armor station.

locations.title: Ice Cream Shop
locations.description: Can be entered through the waterfront or street. Inside, you'll find some junk items, a chem box, and a safe with a master-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Wrecked Boat
locations.description: A boat can be found underneath the flyover here. You'll find a toolbox inside, and be ambushed by a Mirelurk Hunter when you leave.

locations.title: Sunken Plane
locations.description:
A large plane can be found at the bottom of the sea here. Swim into the cockpit to find a first aid kit and steamer trunk.

Looting the trunk will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - Need a Hand](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441320)

locations.title: Underwater Shack
locations.description: A shack can be found on top of a metal platform at the bottom of the ocean here. No loot in the area.

locations.title: Underwater Pier
locations.description: Just outside the playable area, two piers can be found at the bottom of the sea. No loot in the area.

locations.title: Illuminated Pipes
locations.description:
Unlike other pipes on the seafloor, this one has glowing lights on its side. No loot in the area, but may be a remnant of 'Vault 120', an underwater vault (and extended reference to Bioshock) that was cut from the game.

What little information we do have suggests it would have been visited in a quest titled '20 Leagues Under the Sea', and ended in a fight against a giant squid - the vault's overseer.

locations.title: Cat Lover's Boat
locations.description: At the bottom of the sea, you can find an upside-down ship above a ravine. Swim inside the boat to find some cat paintings and 'MEOW!' scrawled into the ceiling.

locations.title: Abandoned Boats
locations.description: Two police boats seemingly apprehended a larger boat here. In the larger boat, you can find a wooden crate, some junk, and a bloodleaf to harvest.

locations.title: Sunken Plane & Recovery Effort
locations.description: A large plane can be found on the seafloor here, and directly above it is a boat and platform that was seemingly trying to salvage the pieces. Inside the boat, you'll find a wooden crate and handful of junk items.

locations.title: Floating Outpost
locations.description: A few boats have been stuck together and turned into an ill-fated outpost here. Search the area for junk items, plants to harvest, a wooden crate, a few mattresses, a suitcase, and a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Sunken Boat
locations.description: A boat carrying several cars has sunk to the bottom of the sea here. No loot in the area.

locations.title: Sunken Boat
locations.description: A boat carrying several containers can be found on the sea floor here. Swim inside to find a lunch pail and some empty milk bottles.

locations.title: Abandoned Boats
locations.description: A half-submerged boat can be found on the surface here, with some smaller wooden boats nearby. One of the wooden boats has an unlocked safe on it.

locations.title: Sunken Containers
locations.description:
A white boat can be found at the bottom of the sea here, with a steamer trunk and medkit inside.

Looting the trunk will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - Predator Becomes Prey](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441390).

locations.title: Underwater Pipe Stash
locations.description:
A pipe can be found at the bottom of the sea. Open the orange hatch on its side to find a first aid kit and steamer trunk inside.

Looting the trunk will complete the miscellaneous quest started when finding the [Bottle Message - Not Going Well](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441394)

locations.title: Lighthouse
locations.description: A leaning lighthouse can be found here. Inside, you can find mirelurk eggs, ammo, junk, an explosives box, a mattress, a 10mm pistol and a safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Campsite
locations.description: Three mattresses and a duffel bag can be found around a campfire here.

locations.title: Tunnel Camp
locations.description: A camp is built into a tunnel here. It's filled with feral ghouls, settler corpses, beds, food items, and junk. You can also find a cooking station, caps stash, and safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Benjamin Franklin Statue
locations.description: An old statue, presumably of Benjamin Franklin, can be found in a sorry state here. You can find a weapon and some junk nearby.

locations.title: The Door
locations.description: A door in the middle of the area has a message for you. Opening it spawns a Sentry Bot that respawns every few days.

locations.title: Crashed Vertibird
locations.description: A wrecked vertibird can be found in the swamp here. A brown flight helmet can be found in the flooded area behind the pilot's seat, and a set of [Power Armor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71737) stands nearby.

locations.title: Swamp Treehouse
locations.description: A shack is built around a tree in the swamp here. It's protected by mirelurks, but inside you can find a mattress, cooking stove, several bottles of moonshine, a laser musket, and a bunch of fusion cells.

locations.title: Skylanes 1665 Mayday Signal Source
locations.description:
Inside the Storage Compartment, an unmarked location within [Skylanes Flight 1665](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71949), found by using a trapdoor between two rows of seats and a cart near a pile of rubble.

Open the hatch next to the ladder to disable the Skylanes 1665 Mayday Signal that's started when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0DB-521](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71997).

The area is also home to a few junk items, glowing fungus, two suitcases (one of which has a novice-difficulty lock), and a wooden crate with a lock of the same level.

locations.title: Gunner Signal Remnant Source
locations.description: A corpse between the seats in a loose chunk of airplane is responsible for the Gunner Signal Remnant. Visited as part of the Best of Three side quest added with the 2024 Next-Gen Content Update, after finding the [Gunner Holotape](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441405). Interact with the gunner corpse here to be ambushed by Caroni who is wielding the [Tesla Cannon](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441410).

locations.title: Parking Garage
locations.description:
An unmarked location that's free of radiation. One half, entered through the blue door, is full of ghouls - you can find food items, suitcases, sleeping bags, a cooking station, and a security gate with a master-difficulty lock hiding a steamer trunk and first aid kit.

The other half, entered through an elevator on the roof, houses a deathclaw alongside a first aid kit and steamer trunk.

locations.title: Wrecked Plane
locations.description: A plane can be found here, with a few military grade circuit boards (and radscorpions) around it.

locations.title: Wrecked Bus
locations.description: A bus can be found here, surrounded by a Glowing One and several ghouls. Loot in and around the bus includes a few suitcases, a duffle bag, and a steamer trunk.

locations.title: Cabin
locations.description: An unmarked cabin and public restroom can be found here. Stingwings can be found guarding the trunk and miscellaneous junk.

locations.title: Wicked Shipping Trailer
locations.description:
The door at the back of a truck trailer has a master-difficulty lock here. It can also be unlocked with a key found at the [Wicked Shipping Fleet Lockup](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71879).

Inside, you'll find a steamer trunk.

locations.title: Dubious Campsite
locations.description: At the edge of the water, you can find a mattress near some barrels. A small wooden crate next to the mattress has a Radaway and some junk in it.

locations.title: Cabin
locations.description: A cabin can be found in the wilderness here. Inside, you'll find enemies, mattresses, a first aid kit, and some other miscellaneous loot containers.

locations.title: Slocum Joe's Basement
locations.description: In the basement of Slocum Joe's, the diner on the street corner. Loot includes junk and miscellaneous containers, but the main attraction is an elevator hidden behind the bookshelf (though it only works after restoring power to [The Switchboard](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=117211), and functions as a quick and easy way to return to that area.)

locations.title: Red Rocket
locations.description: In the middle of Lexington. Search the area in and around it to find an armor workbench, power armor station, weapons workbench, and junk items.

locations.title: Poolside Camp
locations.description: A pool frequented by raiders can be found near the [Lexington Apartments](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71823). Around it, you'll find two sleepings bags and a cooking station, with wild tarberries growing in the water.

locations.title: Walkway Camp
locations.description: On the [raider-occupied](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71698) walkway between buildings you can find two sleeping bags, a chem box, a duffel bag, and a cooler.

locations.title: Bus Station
locations.description: An unmarked bus station can be found by the road here. Loot includes a couple of suitcases and not much else.

locations.title: Wrecked Bus
locations.description: Here, you can find a bus that's gotten stuck at a very convenient angle. By walking up the back of the bus, you can reach the freeway.

locations.title: Camp on the Freeway
locations.description: After getting up onto the elevated freeway via the [Wrecked Bus](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441509), you can follow a series of Railroad murals to find a truck at the eastern edge. Outside, you'll find a cooking station and cooler, while the inside of the trailer has a mattress, first aid kit, tool case, and suitcase.

locations.title: Camp on the Freeway
locations.description: A small camp can be found on top of the elevated freeway here, accessed by walking up the collapsed section a short distance to the west. You'll find a cooking station, bed, some junk items, and a toolbox.

locations.title: Graygarden Homestead
locations.description: An unmarked interior found directly west of [Graygarden](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72050). Inside you'll find several junk and food items, and if you pick through an expert-difficulty lock to access the basement, you'll find a first aid kit, chemistry station, and safe with an advanced-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Abandoned Truck
locations.description: A truck and trailer can be found by the side of the road here. Pick through the advanced-difficulty lock on the trailer door to find an ammo box, mattress, gwinnett brew, and some junk.

locations.title: Trader's Shack
locations.description:
A [Trader](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441514) can be found living in a metal tube beneath the broken freeway here. Their camp consists of a cooking station, sleeping bag, overdue book, a chem box, and some junk items.

There's also a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock between support beams beneath the shack.

locations.title: Operations
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a blue door on the concrete bridge. Inside you'll find several junk items, a wooden crate with a novice-difficulty lock, and a hatch behind a blue barrel in the corner that takes you down to [Reactor Level.](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441517).

locations.title: Boston City Works Beacon Source
locations.description:
Inside [Operations](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441516), accessed by using a hatch behind a blue barrel in the corner. Once inside, turn to the left and use the ham radio to turn off the signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 1DL-109](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71994).

The area is also home to junk and food items.

locations.title: Distress Signal Source
locations.description:
A hatch in the side of an overturned blue train car leads to a small room. Once inside, you can interact with the ham radio to turn off the signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 1DL-109](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71994).

The train car is also home to junk items, a suitcase, and a wooden crate with a novice-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Waystation
locations.description: An unmarked interior entered through a trapdoor in the tower near the train tracks. Inside, you'll find a metal box, machete, chem box, junk, blood pack, and a corpse.

locations.title: Garbled Radio Beacon Source
locations.description:
A cave can be entered here. Before reaching level 20, it's nothing special - home to a few mole rats and brain fungus / glowing fungus growths. 

After hitting level 20 and witnessing a UFO crash, however, the cave contains a wounded alien. You can interact with a ham radio at the back to turn off the signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 1DL-109](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71994).

locations.title: Flooded Boathouse
locations.description: The boathouse by the river here has certainly seen drier days. The boat outside is home a mirelurk nest, ammo box, and a sea captain's hat, while the building (only accessible through doors with advanced-difficulty locks) has a corpse, shock baton, and industrial trunk inside.

locations.title: Freeway Elevator
locations.description: In the wilderness beneath the elevated freeway you can find an elevator that will take you up to the top  where [Power Armor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71738) can be found.

locations.title: Flooded Basement
locations.description: At the bottom of a pile of rubble, you'll find a hole in the side of a building. Poke your head inside to find a mirelurk, several eggs, and a Nuka-Cola machine.

locations.title: Red Rocket
locations.description: An unmarked Red Rocket station. Search the area in and around it to find a power armor station, safe with a novice-difficulty lock, weapons workbench, armor workbench, and plenty of junk items.

locations.title: Plumber's Secret
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through the warehouse's blue doors. Inside you'll find bottlecap mines, junk, a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock, and other miscellaneous loot containers. Look up to the ceiling to find a trail of plungers leading to some wooden boards you can shoot to find a caps stash and syringer rifle.

locations.title: Evans Way Cul-de-Sac
locations.description: A ruined building is home to several raiders here. You'll need to pick through one of three three expert-difficulty locks / gates to reach it, and can find a steamer trunk upstairs.

locations.title: Copley Station
locations.description:
An unmarked location accessed through station entrance on the northern side of the [Boston Public Library](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71844) building, or through the eastern side of the library's interior.

Occupied by Super Mutants.

locations.title: Prost Bar
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a blue door at the bottom of some stairs in the street near [Boston Common](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71960)'s north-western edge. Inside you'll find junk, baseball grenades, and a steamer trunk with a master-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Water Street Apartments
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a white door beneath a large 'apartments' sign. Loot includes food, junk, miscellaneous containers, and mattresses. The upper floor is inaccessible until 'The Silver Shroud' side quest is progressed to a point where you're directed to come here.

locations.title: Boxing Gym
locations.description: Unmarked location entered through a green door on a corner building near [Old North Church](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71870). Loot includes seven instances of Buffout scattered around the gym.

locations.title: Office Building
locations.description: Unmarked location with an interior. Occupied by Raiders.

locations.title: Super Mutant Camp
locations.description: An elevator on top of the building can take you up to the [Fallen Skybridge](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=118765), where super mutants have taken over a gunner camp. Loot mostly consists of junk and corpses.

locations.title: Hub 360
locations.description:
An unmarked location, entered through a door near the rooftop pool or from ground level.

Occupied by super mutants.

locations.title: Ruined Skyscraper
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered by clambering up a fallen corridor on the [Fallen Skybridge](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=118765). Can also be accessed at ground level.

Occupied by Gunners and Super Mutants.

locations.title: Ticker Tape Lounge
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a door on a lower (but still elevated) part of the [Fallen Skybridge](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=118765), or via the rooftop you end up on when using the elevator on top of [Mass Bay Medical Center](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71915). Occupied by Gunners.

Inside you'll find junk, miscellaneous containers, a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock, food, a chemistry station, an overdue book, and a mattress.

locations.title: Pier Building
locations.description: An unmarked building found at the end of the pier near [Donny Kowalski](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=355599). Inside you'll find junk, food, mattresses, and an overdue book.

locations.title: New England Technocrat Society
locations.description:
An additional interior found by going through double doors on the ground floor of the [Harbormaster Hotel](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71833).

Added with the 2024 Next-Gen Content Update, and visited during the [All Hallows' Eve](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441412) side quest.

locations.title: Warehouse
locations.description:
An unmarked location on the pier, entered through a white door facing the green boat. Occupied by Super Mutants.

Expect to find junk and miscellaneous loot containers.

locations.title: Freeway Elevator
locations.description: An alternative way up to the elevated freeway and [Mass Pike Interchange](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71967) can be found at the base of a concrete pillar here.

locations.title: Arcjet Rocket Engine
locations.description: An attached terminal can be used to activate the rocket. Try not to stand too close afterwards.

locations.title: Factory
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through the double doors near some radioactive barrels. Inside you'll find junk, miscellaneous containers, a few hostile insects and a fusion core. 

On the upper floor, picking through a door with a novice-difficulty lock will reveal a safe with a master-difficulty lock and a terminal that can unlock a security door near the entrance. Behind it, you'll find two first aid kits.

locations.title: Fort Hagen Hangar
locations.description:
A hatch at the base of the northern satellite dish can be found behind a security door. A terminal on the walkway directly above it can be used to open the door, though it only appears during the [Headhunting](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442288) quest.

*Automatron DLC Required.*

locations.title: Institute Reactor
locations.description:
**Leads To:** [Institute Reactor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442605)

Institute Advanced Systems - at the end of a corridor blocked by lasers. Only accessible during 'The Nuclear Option' quest (via the [Brotherhood](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350618), [Railroad](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350817), or [Minutemen](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350738)) or the 'Powering Up' quest for the Institute.

locations.title: Public Works Maintenance Area
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through an underwater pipe. Inside, you'll find an advanced-difficulty terminal with a steamer trunk behind it.

If you side with the Minutemen, you'll come here during [The Nuclear Option](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350738) and have access to its more expansive sections. A more detailed map of the area can be found [here](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442634).

locations.title: The Institute
locations.description: **Leads To:** [The Institute](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442640)

locations.title: Public Works Maintenance Area (Exit Only)
locations.description: You'll emerge from this pipe during [The Nuclear Option (Minutemen)](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=350738) after fighting your way through the [Public Works Maintenance Area](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442635).

locations.title: CIT Rotunda
locations.description:
An unmarked location that can be entered from multiple angles. Inside you'll find junk, miscellaneous containers, a mattress, food, an industrial trunk, a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock, and a mini nuke.

Occupied by Synths and Super Mutants.

locations.title: Pumphouse
locations.description: An unmarked location with a separate interior map accessible from the concrete building near the river. Loot includes a [Fusion Core](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71529), steamer trunk, and [The Gainer](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71799).

locations.title: Quincy Police Lock Up
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a door in the corner of [Quincy Police Station](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71973)'s ground floor. Inside you'll find junk, some bottles of whiskey, [Eddie Winter Holotape 3](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=118780), a first aid kit with a novice-difficulty lock, and a police protectron that can be activated with a terminal.

locations.title: Clothes Store
locations.description: Unmarked location. Inside you'll find a cooking stove, armor workbench, a bed, junk, miscellaneous containers, and several pieces of apparel and armor on the shelves.

locations.title: University Credit Union
locations.description:
An unmarked location at the edge of [University Point](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71847). Entering from the front will give you access to a suitcase, 10mm pistol, stimpak, and some junk.

Entering from the side (done by hacking a novice-level terminal in the neighbouring building) grants access to the novice-difficulty vault control terminal. Once inside, hack a safe with a master-difficulty lock to find a button - this opens a secret room where you'll find [Prototype UP77 "Limitless Potential" [Laser gun]](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71763), a chemistry station, and a weapons workbench.

locations.title: University Point: Sedgwick Hall
locations.description: An unmarked location directly west of the main [University Point](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71847) marker.

locations.title: Small Shack
locations.description: A small metal shack can be found at the north-western edge of [Lake Quannapowitt](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71978). Mirelurks patrol the outside, while the inside is home to  junk, a toolbox with a novice-difficulty lock, some notes, and a terminal.

locations.title: Back Alley Bowling
locations.description: An unmarked location directly opposite the large Mr Handy statue in the [General Atomics Galleria](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71817).

locations.title: Wicked Shipping Trailer
locations.description: A large truck can be found here. In the trailer you'll find a steamer trunk, four RadAways, and an Explosives Box - just be ready for plenty of Rads, as there's a few radioactive barrels in the back too.

locations.title: Campsite
locations.description: An unmarked camp has been set up next to a truck in the wilderness. You'll find a duffel bag, ammo box, and some mattresses.

locations.title: Reactor Level
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a hatch opposite the [Fusion Core](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71479) generator in the [Mass Fusion Containment Shed](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71882). Hidden behind some radioactive barrels.

Once inside, you can interact with the circuit breaker to turn off the Automated Radio Alarm signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Radio Tower 3SM-U81](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71990).

locations.title: Kendall Parking
locations.description: An unmarked location accessed by using a white door beneath a large 'P' sign near the entrance to [Greenetech Genetics](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71822). Inside you'll find mole rats with land mines strapped to their backs, junk, a chem cooler, food, and a sleeping bag - all owned by a Drifter who's friends with the 'ratties'.

locations.title: Distress Signal Source
locations.description:
A secret room in [Fallon's Department Store](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71819) can be found while exploring the jewellery shop in the basement. Press the button beneath the desk to move aside a bookshelf in the south-west corner.

Inside you'll find six safes; two with Master-difficulty locks, and four with Advanced-difficulty locks, all of which can be unlocked with [Fallon's Storage Key](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442705) in a nearby toolbox. There's also a ham radio that you can interact with to disable the Distress Signal found when extending the satellites at [Relay Tower 0SC-527](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71991)

locations.title: Parking Garage
locations.description:
An unmarked location a short walk north-east of [Fallon's Department Store](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71819). Inside you'll find a deadly maze filled with traps, puzzles, corpses, ghouls, and miscellaneous loot.

Reach the top floor to find a [Hot Rodder](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71463) magazine in a small shack, and two cells full of rewards (a Mini Nuke and four Fusion Cores, or chems and first aid). Press the button next to the cell you want to open, but prepare for the other cell's loot to be destroyed.

locations.title: Miller Family Radio Signal Source
locations.description:
Inside the Shelter found in an overturned blue train carriage at [Big John's Salvage](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71920). Initially sealed shut - follow the electrical wires to a circuit breaker behind a nearby building, and pull the switch to gain access.

Once inside, you can interact with a ham radio to turn off the Miller Family Radio Signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0SC-527](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71991).

Other findings include a Railway Rifle, mattress, [Big John's Safe Key](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442711), and some junk.

locations.title: Supermutant Radio Broadcast Source
locations.description:
[Shaw High School](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72024)  A hatch labelled 'storage' can be found in the basement, entered through a door in the corner of the cafeteria on the ground floor. Once inside, you can interact with the ham radio to turn off the signal activated when you extend the satellites at [Relay Tower 0SC-527](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71991).

The area is also home to junk items, corpses, and a combat knife.

locations.title: Propane Store
locations.description: An unmarked building near the road. A cooking station can be found outside, while the inside is home to a Nuka-Cola machine, sleeping bag, food, junk, and safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Apartment
locations.description:
An unmarked location entered through a white door on the rooftop. To reach it, use the stairs outside a building to the west, and walk along the roofs and walkways connecting them.

Inside you'll find junk, food, a toolbox with a novice-difficulty lock, and a [holotape](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442719).

locations.title: Subway Station
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through a street-level subway entrance. Inside you'll find a caps stash, junk and two instances of Day Tripper.

locations.title: Joe's Spuckies
locations.description:
An unmarked location north-east of [Postal Square](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72014), entered through a door at the end of a curved wall. Occupied by Gunners.

Inside you'll find sleeping bags, a trunk, chems, a caps stash, several glowing fungus growths, a weapons workbench, and an armor workbench.

locations.title: Slim's Camp
locations.description: An unmarked location inhabited by [Slim](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442726), a chem dealer. Search the area to find a sleeping bag, chemistry station, power armor station, weapons workbench, cooking station, and miscellaneous junk / food.

locations.title: South Boston
locations.description: [Andrew Station](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71926) exit - returns you to the open world.

locations.title: Joe's Spuckies Sandwich Shop
locations.description: A hatch at the top of a ladder. Unlocked with [Joe's Spuckies Basement Key](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442732)

locations.title: Joe's Spuckies Sandwich Shop
locations.description: A hatch behind the counter, held shut with a master-difficulty lock, leads down to the [Southie Speakeasy](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442733). It can be unlocked with [Joe's Spuckies Basement Key](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=442732) found by exploring to the end of [Andrew Station](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71926).

locations.title: Commonwealth
locations.description: [Boston Mayoral Shelter](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71858) exit - returns you to the open world.

locations.title: Pearwood Residences
locations.description: Unmarked location

locations.title: Church
locations.description: An unmarked location entered through cellar doors in the church's graveyard. Inside you'll find ghouls, cats, junk, a cooler, and an ammo box.

locations.title: Boston Mayoral Shelter - Lower Level
locations.description: **Leads To:** [Boston Mayoral Shelter - Lower Level](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=443328)

locations.title: Boston Mayoral Shelter - Upper Level
locations.description: **Leads To:** [Boston Mayoral Shelter - Upper Level](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=443327)

locations.title: Train Carriage Camp
locations.description: Here, you'll find an unmarked camp where a settler has set up camp inside a shipping container on the back of a train carriage. Search the area to find food, junk, a mattress, and a safe with an expert-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Raider Graveyard
locations.description: A tiny unmarked graveyard can be found here, with a raider kneeling over their fallen comrade.

locations.title: Campsite
locations.description: An unmarked camp with three mattresses, a suitcase, and a cooking station.

locations.title: Shack
locations.description: An unmarked shack can be found in the wilderness here. Search it to find a toolbox, locker, brain fungus, ammo box, tool case, and some radroaches.

locations.title: Train Carriage Camp
locations.description: A derailed blue train carriage has a novice-difficulty lock on the door. Pick it open to find a mattress, cooler, and wooden crate.

locations.title: Pulowski Preservation Shelter Cluster
locations.description: Five Pulowski Preservation Shelters can be found around a port-a-diner in this unmarked area. Search the area to find a suitcase and cooler.

locations.title: Crashed UFO
locations.description: Appears here after level 20. Its little green pilot can be found in a cave to the north [here](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441526).

locations.title: Campsite
locations.description: An unmarked camp in the parking lot with three mattresses, a toolbox, and a cooking station.

locations.title: Jamaica Plain Town Hall Basement
locations.description:
An unmarked interior found in the basement of the town hall west of [Jamaica Plain](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72054).

Pick through the advanced-difficulty lock or use the [Jamaica Plain Town Hall Key](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=443597) to get inside.

locations.title: Wicked Shipping Trailer
locations.description:
The door at the back of a truck trailer has a master-difficulty lock here. It can also be unlocked with a key found at the [Wicked Shipping Fleet Lockup](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71879).

Inside you'll find a steamer trunk, stealth boy, bottlecap mine, and gas mask with goggles.

locations.title: Freeway Elevator
locations.description: A yellow platform in a fenced-off area can take you up to the freeway here.

locations.title: Camp on the Freeway
locations.description: An unmarked camp accessed via the [Freeway Elevator](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=443611). Search it to find a safe with a master-difficulty lock, chemistry station, mattress, caps stash, cooking station, and plenty of junk.

locations.title: Hawthorne Estate
locations.description: An unmarked location, entered through a red building's white door.

locations.title: Raider Camp
locations.description: An unmarked raider camp can be found here.

locations.title: Warren Theater
locations.description: Unmarked location entered through a red door near the 'Foodstuffs' sign. Inside you'll find junk, food, a first aid box, Day Tripper, and a safe with an advanced-difficulty lock.

locations.title: Elevator
locations.description: A yellow platform next to the building can take you up to the rooftop.

locations.title: Dugout Inn
locations.description: [Diamond City Market](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71968) - behind the All Faiths Chapel.

locations.title: Colonial Taphouse
locations.description: An unmarked bar found on the upper level of [Diamond City](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=193929).

locations.title: Kellogg's House
locations.description: On the outskirts of [Diamond City](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=193929). Can be entered by picking through the master-difficulty lock on the door, or having it unlocked for you during [Getting a Clue](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=354339).

locations.title: Diner
locations.description:
An unmarked location above the junkyard near [Diamond City](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=193929). Easiest to reach with a jetpack, or by performing some very tricky jumps over the rooftops of nearby buildings.

Inside you'll find a power armor station, bed, junk, and [Mini Nuke](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=443801).

locations.title: Anna's Cafe
locations.description: An unmarked diner can be found next to the road here. Inside you'll find food, junk, a first aid box, a sleeping bag, and a 10mm pistol.

locations.title: Car Tree
locations.description: An unmarked location where a few cars are stuck in a tree's branches. Search the base of the tree to find sleeping bags, a cooking station, and a  duffle bag.

locations.title: Super Mutant Camp
locations.description: An unmarked building has been taken over by Super Mutants. Search it to find raider corpses, junk, meat bags, a first aid kit, and bed. On the top floor, you can find a steamer trunk.

locations.title: Garage Playground
locations.description: An unmarked location where you can find a playground (occasionally inhabited by raiders). Search the area to find sleeping bags inside the UFO, and a garage with a power armor station, weapons workbench, junk, and miscellaneous containers inside.

locations.title: Floating Outpost
locations.description: A small outpost can be found floating here. Search it to find miscellaneous containers, junk, plants, food, and two sleeping bags.

locations.title: Joes Spuckies Coffee Shop
locations.description: An unmarked diner filled with junk, food, and a cooler.

locations.title: Painted Statue
locations.description:
A raider can be found painting a statue here. Search the area to find a cooking station, sleeping bag, day tripper, alcohol, and suitcase. 

You can also find a chem cooler in the statue's hand.

locations.title: Wrecked Rowboat
locations.description: A rowboat has washed ashore here. Inside you'll find a cooler and some junk.

locations.title: Mole Rat Nest
locations.description:
A small above-ground nest can be found here, with mole rats protecting it.

Search the nest to find a duffel bag and some corpses you can loot.

locations.title: Destroyed House
locations.description:
A wrecked house can be found next to the railway, with wild mongrels protecting it. 

Search it to find a cooler, junk, and brain fungus growth.

locations.title: Cottage
locations.description:
An unmarked location by the waterfront.

Search it to find a baseball bat, junk, combat rifle, and a single raider.

locations.title: Forged Camp
locations.description: An unmarked camp in the woods, inhabited by a small group of Forge enemies. Visited during [Pyromaniac](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=441416), a quest added in the 2024 Next-Gen Content Update.

locations.title: Makeshift Camp
locations.description: An unmarked camp, featuring a small overhang attached to some trees. Search the area to find a duffle bag and flip lighter, with a settler sometimes in the area too.

locations.title: Military Vehicles
locations.description: An unmarked location where some military vehicles lay by the roadside, protected by robots. Search the vehicle on the truck bed to find an ammo box and wooden crate inside.

locations.title: Gunner Camp
locations.description:
An unmarked gunner camp can be found on the flyover here. 

Search it to find beds, a first aid kit, power armor station, weapons workbench, and large toolbox.

locations.title: Wrecked Bus
locations.description: A large yellow bus lays by the road here. Step inside to loot a first aid kit next to the driver's seat.

locations.title: Hilltop Supplies
locations.description: Search the top of this hill to find an open safe holding two ammo boxes.

locations.title: Concord Pharmacy
locations.description:
An unmarked, wrecked building with a 'drugs' sign outside.

Search it to find a first aid kid on the ground floor, then head upstairs for an ammo box, tool case, and safe with an expert-difficulty lock in the wall.

locations.title: Irradiated Thistle Field
locations.description: A basket holding junk, food, and a RadAway can be found near some irradiated thistles here. Be careful when harvesting the plants, as they can begin spewing radiation if you stand too close.

locations.title: Destroyed House
locations.description: An unmarked house is all but gone, with only two walls left behind. Watch out for a Bloodbug as you loot some mentats, junk, buffout, and a toolbox.

locations.title: Deathclaw Nest
locations.description:
A deathclaw has built a nest beneath the rocky overhang here.

Search the area to find some corpses, and loot the nest itself to find a Deathclaw Egg.

locations.title: Submerged House
locations.description:
A wrecked house and its long-dead inhabitant can be found just off the south-western shore of [Spectacle Island](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72056) here.

Loot mainly consists of junk and a bottle of vodka, but two bottles of Nuka-Cola Quantum can be found in the rubble near the fridge. Swim near it to knock them loose.

locations.title: Raider Shack
locations.description: A short walk south-west of [Sunshine Tidings Co-op](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=72029).  Note that you may be ambushed by two raiders when approaching.

locations.title: Boobytrapped Safe
locations.description: A safe with a master-difficulty lock can be found in front of Lexington Apartments, surrounded by wrecked cars and protected by two land mines.

locations.title: Wrecked Train
locations.description: Multiple carriages have split apart here. Search them to find ammo boxes, a wooden crate, and some [Power Armor](https://fallout4map.com?locationIds=71699).

locations.title: Shack Beneath the Flyover
locations.description:
Home of a Radscorpion.

Search it to find a bed, gum drops, junk, welding goggles, and tool case. Outside, there's a cage with an expert-difficulty lock holding four Radaway and a caps stash.

locations.title: Cabins
locations.description:
Search them to find a steamer trunk, cooler, mattress, miscellaneous containers, and food.

Outside, you'll find a cooking station and _creative_ outhouse.

locations.title: Lakeside Cabin
locations.description: Search it to find a toolbox, chem box, a suitcase with a novice-difficulty lock, and some junk. A cooler can be found at the end of the nearby pier.

**Required:** Walk up and pet the good boy (ask Dogmeat to follow)

**Companion Quest:** None

**Romanceable?** No

**Affinity Interests:** None; Dogmeat has no concerns for human affairs

Unlike other companions, Dogmeat has no affinity system; instead of earning the companion perk through behavior, you must spend skill points on the level-up perk chart.

**Companion Perk:** Attack Dog (CH 4)
1. [LVL 1] Your faithful canine companion can hold an enemy, giving you a greater chance to hit them in V.A.T.S.
2. [LVL 9] When your dog holds an enemy, there's a chance he'll cripple the limb he's biting.
3. [LVL 25] When your dog holds an enemy, there's a chance he'll cause them to bleed.
4. [LVL 31] When adventuring with your dog, you take 10% less damage.
